                "invention-title": [
                    "Hydrogen combustion system based on carbon dioxide as cycle fluid",
                    "基于二氧化碳作为循环工质的氢燃烧系统"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to the technical field of hydrogen combustion systems, and discloses a hydrogen combustion system based on carbon dioxide as a cycle fluid. According to the technical scheme, the device comprises a prime mover system device, hydrogen serves as fuel to be combusted in the prime mover system device, high-temperature flue gas is generated after combustion, and the high-temperature flue gas comprises trace oxygen, carbon dioxide and water; the waste heat utilization device, the gas-liquid separator, the flue gas analysis device and the first gas mixer are connected with the prime motor system device, and the first gas mixer is provided with a carbon dioxide and oxygen inlet and used for introducing carbon dioxide and oxygen and mixing the carbon dioxide and the oxygen with separated flue gas so as to adjust the proportion of the oxygen and the carbon dioxide and generate circulating flue gas; and the circulating flue gas is guided into the gas inlet end of the prime mover system device to be mixed with hydrogen for combustion. On the basis that carbon dioxide serves as a cycle working medium, the structures of an existing gas turbine generator set and an existing gas internal combustion engine generator set are not changed, and efficient, low-cost and high-scale utilization of hydrogen energy is achieved."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及氢燃烧系统技术领域，公开了基于二氧化碳作为循环工质的氢燃烧系统。其技术方案包括原动机系统装置，氢气作为燃料在原动机系统装置内燃烧，燃烧后产生高温烟气，所述高温烟气的成分为微量氧气、二氧化碳和水；还包括与原动机系统装置连接的余热利用装置、气液分离器、烟气分析装置和第一气体混合器，第一气体混合器具有二氧化碳和氧气进入口，用于通入二氧化碳和氧气并与分离后的烟气混合，以调节氧气和二氧化碳的配比，生成循环烟气，将循环烟气导入原动机系统装置的进气端以与氢气混合燃烧。本发明基于以二氧化碳作为循环工质，不改变现有燃气轮机发电机组和燃气内燃机发电机组的构造，实现氢能的高效、低成本、高规模化利用。"
                }
            ]
